Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.38,0:00:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.49,0:00:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We have some encouraging things \Nto look forward to in this month’s program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.23,0:00:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll hear the experiences \Nof Sister Agapita Reyes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.70,0:00:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As a Christian wife and mother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.70,0:00:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,she successfully met the challenges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.70,0:00:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of raising a family \Nby applying Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.84,0:00:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped her \Nto remain steadfast throughout her life?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you maintain focus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.01,0:00:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,even after you achieve a spiritual goal? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.15,0:00:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Could subtle temptations \Nand distractions take you off course? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.09,0:00:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll discuss an important quality \Nthat can help you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.66,0:00:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents are proud of young ones \Nwho give their best to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.33,0:00:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Their feelings are \Na reflection of how Jehovah feels \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.30,0:00:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and are the inspiration \Nfor this month’s music video. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.30,0:00:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting for August 2017.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.53,0:01:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The complexity found in nature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.56,0:01:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,has inspired \Namazing achievements in technology.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.10,0:01:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But it has also moved people to ask, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Was It Designed?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.34,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the title of an Awake! series \Nthat first appeared in 2008. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.18,0:01:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a powerful tool \Nto turn people’s attention to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.91,0:01:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the Creator of all things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.92,0:01:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re pleased to introduce the first \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.12,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in an exciting new video series \Nbased on those articles.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.05,0:02:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The trunk of the African elephant \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is an impressive multitool. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.15,0:02:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It is both flexible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.39,0:02:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and strong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.69,0:02:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It can pick up a blade of grass \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.50,0:02:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or uproot a tree.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.44,0:02:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Some elephants can use \Ntheir trunks to feed themselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.27,0:02:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,around 270 kilograms (600 lbs) \Nof vegetation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.18,0:02:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,every day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.19,0:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With their trunks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they can suck water like a straw, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.30,0:03:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,spray like a fountain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and swim with a snorkel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The trunk can give a gentle touch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,give a strong push, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or sound a warning trumpet.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.09,0:03:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Engineers admire \Nthe elephant trunk’s remarkable flexibility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.39,0:03:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This comes from having no bone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.89,0:03:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it contains \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about 150,000 muscle units\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—an incredible marriage \Nof strength and structure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.31,0:03:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspired by the elephant’s trunk,\Nresearchers are designing robots\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for the future with greater flexibility.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Industrial design\Noften can be made better by copying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.02,0:03:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfectly beautiful solutions \Nin the natural world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:04:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.19,0:04:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the elephant’s trunk evolve? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Or . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.17,0:04:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This new video series can help you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.24,0:04:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the proof that there is a Creator. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.74,0:04:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It can especially help \Nyou young ones to recognize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and reject \Nthe false teaching of evolution. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Use these new videos \Nin your personal study \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.15,0:04:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and share them \Nwith classmates and teachers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.42,0:04:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll help you \Ngive an effective witness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.02,0:04:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring honor to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find them \Nin the Video on Demand section \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.16,0:04:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.83,0:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones need strong faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.40,0:04:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in this difficult system of things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.14,0:04:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are not alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.14,0:04:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They have Jehovah’s holy spirit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a congregation of brothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:05:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and very often, \Nloving Christian parents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.28,0:05:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In Monterrey, Mexico, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.55,0:05:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Agapita Reyes \Nset a beautiful example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.99,0:05:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in building up \Nthe faith of her children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.83,0:05:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What circumstances \Nmade that effort a special challenge?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.00,0:05:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not easy raising kids in the truth,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.77,0:05:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had ten. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.68,0:05:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned the truth when I was 19. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.05,0:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Witnesses came to preach in our town, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.12,0:05:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and my father offered them a place to stay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.42,0:05:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke with them all through the night \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.96,0:05:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and then announced excitedly \Nthat he had found the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.93,0:05:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I was baptized in the 1950’s.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.03,0:05:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was favorable toward the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.30,0:05:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but got involved \Nin political affairs in the community, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.61,0:05:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and from there \Nhe began his political career. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When I read 1 Peter 3:1, 2, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.48,0:06:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood that I needed \Nto be in subjection to my husband, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.15,0:06:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with the hope that he could be won over \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“without a word” by means of my conduct.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.82,0:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When my children were young, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.82,0:06:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a weekly Bible study program \Nfor each of them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.66,0:06:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and as they grew up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.66,0:06:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the older kids helped me \Nwith their younger siblings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.83,0:06:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember Mom always made \Nan effort to teach me how to preach.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.30,0:06:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I would write presentations \Nfor the ministry on pieces of paper, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.51,0:06:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kids would practice while they \Ndid their chores around the house. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.81,0:06:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We set aside time \None day a week for our family study.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be anything\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—a sack of potatoes, \Na sack of flour, or a house plant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.99,0:06:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She would tell me: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.39,0:06:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Imagine that this is a person \Nyou meet in field service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you say to them?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When I finished, she would say to me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“The way you did it just now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.26,0:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,do it like that when you \Ngo out in the ministry.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.20,0:07:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom was very creative. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.70,0:07:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She would assign us to play \Nthe part of different Bible characters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.14,0:07:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom taught us to appreciate the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.81,0:07:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,through her example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I served as a regular pioneer for many years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.69,0:07:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I encouraged my kids \Nto reach out for spiritual goals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter left home at the age of 18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.59,0:07:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve as a special pioneer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, my oldest son did the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.50,0:07:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,These two proved to be excellent examples \Nfor their younger brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Raising my son Noé was a challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.11,0:07:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the youngest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.81,0:07:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and at a very young age, \Nhe was diagnosed with epilepsy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite his limitations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.15,0:07:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he was able to serve \Nas a ministerial servant \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and regular pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He fought his illness for more than 40 years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,before passing away recently.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.36,0:08:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Losing my husband in death \Ndealt me another blow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now my health and my memory are fading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.87,0:08:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t do as much \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ministry as before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But even so, thanks to the help \Nof the brothers in the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.44,0:08:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not giving up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.75,0:08:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though my husband \Nwas not a Witness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.62,0:08:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I respected him \Nas the head of the family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never forget the moment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.09,0:08:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when my husband asked me \Nto study the Bible with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.16,0:08:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember \Nthat my eldest son gave the talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.96,0:08:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and his father was \Namong the candidates for baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.03,0:08:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two years \Nafter I received the Kingdom message, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.77,0:08:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,my husband was baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.61,0:08:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Another great blessing \Nwas seeing my children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.84,0:08:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,grow in the truth \Nand use their youth to serve Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.45,0:08:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Some have served as special pioneers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,circuit overseers, or in Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.29,0:08:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn’t for her help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.29,0:09:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the support of my siblings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.32,0:09:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps we wouldn’t be part \Nof the organization today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.33,0:09:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to her, \Nwe started out on the best course in life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.57,0:09:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Words cannot express \Nhow grateful I am to her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.21,0:09:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I now find great joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in seeing my grandchildren \Nand great-grandchildren \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.55,0:09:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,follow their parents’ example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.91,0:09:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking about all I have experienced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.98,0:09:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in over 60 years of service to Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.85,0:09:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—raising my ten children in the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,my husband becoming a servant of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing 30 members \Nof my family in full-time service—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do nothing \Nbut thank Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.86,0:09:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for his blessings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.00,0:09:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been worth all the effort.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Reyes continues \Nto serve Jehovah faithfully \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.98,0:10:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at 86 years of age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you personally experienced \Nsome of her more difficult struggles? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s felt the heartbreak \Nof losing her husband and a child in death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In recent years, \Nshe’s battled failing health. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.73,0:10:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But through all of that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.97,0:10:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Reyes remains \Na motivating example for Christian women. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.47,0:10:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Her story is an excellent start \Nto our discussion.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.31,0:10:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme for our program is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.31,0:10:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Women Proclaiming the Good News.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.65,0:10:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, throughout human history \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.79,0:10:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,women have been subjected \Nto injustice, violence, and abuse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.79,0:10:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible explains. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.90,0:10:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the latter part of Genesis 3:16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,notice what God says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.17,0:10:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your longing will be for your husband, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.37,0:11:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will dominate you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When God said \Nthat Adam would “dominate” his wife, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.48,0:11:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,God was not indicating His approval \Nof the subjugation of woman by man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.49,0:11:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He was simply foretelling \Nthe sad consequences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.49,0:11:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of sin on the first couple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.33,0:11:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So abuse of women \Nis a direct outcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.00,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sinful nature of humans, \Nnot of God’s will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right down to our day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,rarely have women been accorded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.67,0:11:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the dignity that God \Nwants them to receive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.18,0:11:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Jehovah makes clear \Nin his Word, the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.05,0:11:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that women and men \Nhave equal standing before him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.02,0:11:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he indicated \Nthat women would play a vital role \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.26,0:11:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the outworking of his purpose.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.76,0:11:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Our theme is based on Psalm 68:11. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:11:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.83,0:12:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah gives the command; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.57,0:12:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the women proclaiming \Nthe good news are a large army.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.08,0:12:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Those words were inspired by God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.41,0:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what did the psalmist \Nhave in mind when he penned them?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.35,0:12:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The context of Psalm 68 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.02,0:12:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,shows that David was praising \NJehovah as a God of saving acts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,From the time of their Exodus from Egypt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.63,0:12:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the men of Israel often had to fight \Nagainst enemy nations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.66,0:12:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help, \Nthey defeated them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the entire nation would then rejoice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,over the victory Jehovah had given them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.91,0:12:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The first of the victory celebrations \Nrecorded in the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.11,0:12:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was at the time \Nthat Jehovah gave his people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.75,0:12:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the victory over Pharaoh \Nand the Egyptians who were pursuing them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.72,0:12:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Exodus 15:20, 21 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.72,0:12:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,tells what happened \Nafter this miraculous victory: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Miriam the prophetess, \NAaron’s sister, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.73,0:13:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“took a tambourine in her hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.97,0:13:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“and all the women followed her \Nwith tambourines and with dances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Miriam sang in response to the men: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.84,0:13:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Sing to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.95,0:13:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘for he has become highly exalted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.28,0:13:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The horse and its rider \Nhe has hurled into the sea.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.89,0:13:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture that scene. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.46,0:13:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There were \Nan estimated three million people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.06,0:13:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nation of Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.06,0:13:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine\N—out of that large number, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.66,0:13:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“all the women” were dancing \Nand singing praises to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That was undoubtedly a large army! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What a great shout of praise \Nto Jehovah that was!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.31,0:13:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Another example was \Nwhen King Saul and his general David \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.68,0:13:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,returned from victory over the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.62,0:13:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read the account \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.65,0:14:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 18:6. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.19,0:14:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“When David and the others would return \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.33,0:14:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“from striking down the Philistines, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“the women would come out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.30,0:14:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“from all the cities of Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“with song and dances to meet King Saul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.94,0:14:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“with tambourines, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.94,0:14:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with rejoicing, and with lutes.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.74,0:14:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that the account says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that the women came out of “all the cities” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.45,0:14:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to greet them with music, song, and dance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.28,0:14:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasions such as these \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.39,0:14:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,were not simply expressions of rejoicing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.16,0:14:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that originated with human emotion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall that under inspiration, David said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.16,0:14:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah gives the command; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.17,0:14:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the women proclaiming \Nthe good news are a large army.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.14,0:14:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and Jehovah valued \Ntheir expressions of praise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.67,0:14:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just as he valued the contributions \Nof the men who had engaged in battle.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.01,0:14:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What about today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.55,0:15:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The report for the 2017 service year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.08,0:15:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,shows that there were \Nover 8.3 million publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.99,0:15:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,proclaiming the good news \Nthroughout the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.69,0:15:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that in most lands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.70,0:15:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not unusual for our dear sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to make up over half \Nof our special pioneers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.23,0:15:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and nearly three quarters of those \Nwho serve in the regular pioneer work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.84,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, many other sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.24,0:15:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are wholeheartedly spreading \Nthe good news of the Kingdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best of their ability \Nwithin their circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many single-parent families \Nwhere our sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are providing materially \Nand spiritually for their children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.26,0:15:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of our faithful single sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are expending themselves \Nin Jehovah’s service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.06,0:15:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in theocratic construction \Nand maintenance work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.57,0:15:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel service, \Nand serving where the need is greater\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,—which includes \Nserving in foreign-language fields. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.87,0:16:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Faithful wives \Nloyally support their husbands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.71,0:16:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as fulfill their own roles \Nas preachers and teachers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, how Jehovah must be pleased \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.79,0:16:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to see all of you \Nwho serve in various ways! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.22,0:16:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re grateful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for the warm spirit and positive influence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our dear sisters have on our congregations.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.17,0:16:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah values \Nthis “large army” of sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.97,0:16:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But does he take note \Nof the individual circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.91,0:16:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and sacrifices of each sister? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.08,0:16:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not have to wonder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.58,0:16:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of his Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.82,0:16:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah makes it evident that he sees \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and appreciates each of his servants.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.92,0:16:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.96,0:16:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,did you notice when we read \Nthe scripture in Exodus chapter 15 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that Miriam was described \Nas a “prophetess”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:17:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Evidently, \Nshe was privileged to be used \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.27,0:17:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as an instrument \Nof divine communication. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.07,0:17:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In some instances, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.77,0:17:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this no doubt included singing songs \Nthat were inspired by Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.45,0:17:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Miriam was not the only one \Nin the Scriptures with this designation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.28,0:17:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Other women in the Bible record, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.55,0:17:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Anna and Isaiah’s wife, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,were also spoken of as prophetesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book of Judges, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,another faithful servant, \NDeborah, is identified. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.10,0:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read Judges 4:4, 5: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.71,0:17:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now Deborah, a prophetess, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.88,0:17:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“the wife of Lappidoth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.88,0:17:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“was judging Israel at that time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.25,0:17:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“She used to sit under Deborah’s palm tree \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.95,0:17:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“between Ramah and Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.95,0:17:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the mountainous region of Ephraim; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.09,0:17:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the Israelites \Nwould go up to her for judgment.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.79,0:17:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Evidently, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:18:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Deborah was assigned to settle \Ndisputes that arose among Israelites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.80,0:18:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving Jehovah’s answer \Nto problems that came up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.47,0:18:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Much later in Israel’s history, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.40,0:18:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,during the reign of faithful King Josiah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huldah served as a prophetess. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.84,0:18:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At 2 Kings 22:8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.85,0:18:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we read that while the temple \Nwas being repaired, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.35,0:18:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the original book of the Law was found. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When it was read to Josiah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.63,0:18:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he was distraught at seeing how far off \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.90,0:18:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the nation had strayed from Jehovah’s Law. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.06,0:18:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 13, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.33,0:18:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he directed the priest, the secretary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.60,0:18:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and other influential men: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.84,0:18:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go, inquire of Jehovah in my behalf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“in behalf of the people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.88,0:18:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“and in behalf of all Judah \Nconcerning the words of this book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.62,0:18:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been found.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.42,0:19:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they accomplish this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.82,0:19:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 14 continues: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.73,0:19:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Hilkiah the priest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.93,0:19:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Ahikam, Achbor, Shaphan, and Asaiah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.57,0:19:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,went to Huldah the prophetess.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.24,0:19:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting that Jehovah \Nused this faithful woman \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.24,0:19:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to convey his direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and that prominent men and priests \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.61,0:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sought her divinely inspired advice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.98,0:19:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The Christian Greek Scriptures, however, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.58,0:19:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,do not permit sisters \Nto serve in such a capacity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.32,0:19:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as did Deborah \Nand other prophetesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nation of Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.99,0:19:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.99,0:19:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Titus 2:3, 4 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.56,0:19:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,encourages “older women” \Nto display spiritual qualities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.57,0:19:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that they may advise \Nthe younger women” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.94,0:19:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read those verses: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.08,0:19:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Likewise, let the older women \Nbe reverent in behavior, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.48,0:20:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“not slanderous, \Nnot enslaved to a lot of wine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“teachers of what is good, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.92,0:20:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that they may advise \Nthe younger women \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to love their husbands,\Nto love their children.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.09,0:20:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How we appreciate \Nthe spiritually mature sisters among us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.57,0:20:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who provide \Nsuch fine assistance to younger sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.24,0:20:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or those who are newer in the truth!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.87,0:20:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, today Jehovah \Nhas delegated authority to men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.81,0:20:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They Scripturally qualify \Nto serve as elders and ministerial servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.15,0:20:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to serve, guide, \Nand protect his people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.02,0:20:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is obvious that this is not due \Nto a lack of respect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.76,0:20:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for the gifts of our sisters \Nin the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.29,0:20:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, \Nmany responsible brothers will acknowledge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have benefited \Nfrom the experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.53,0:20:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and practical wisdom \Nof our humble, spiritually mature sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.24,0:20:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.24,0:21:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,think of the outstanding faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of another woman \Nmentioned in the Bible, Mary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.25,0:21:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What an awesome responsibility \NJehovah entrusted her with\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—bearing and raising \Nhis own Son as a human! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only imagine the thoughts \Nthat were going through her mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.36,0:21:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when she was told of this assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.40,0:21:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But the account in Luke chapter 1 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.40,0:21:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,tells us much about her spirituality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.51,0:21:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 38, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.94,0:21:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,after the angel Gabriel \Nfinished speaking with her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.72,0:21:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary’s response was simply: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.42,0:21:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look! Jehovah’s slave girl! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.92,0:21:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,May it happen to me \Naccording to your declaration.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She must have wondered \Nhow Jehovah would accomplish these things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.06,0:21:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but she was humble and obedient. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.33,0:22:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Faithful men such as Moses \Nand Jeremiah hesitated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.04,0:22:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when given \Na challenging assignment from God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.21,0:22:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Mary! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.21,0:22:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful example \Nshe set for all of us\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.94,0:22:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—men and women!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.85,0:22:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, \NJehovah has always highly valued women. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.85,0:22:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are privileged to serve today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.12,0:22:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with millions of hardworking sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.56,0:22:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How pleased Jehovah must be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.56,0:22:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to see dear sisters \Nserving him humbly and faithfully! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.33,0:22:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We urge you sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.33,0:22:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,please keep up your good work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.17,0:22:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and continue to be \Na positive influence in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.71,0:22:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,God has indeed granted \Nyou faithful women \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.88,0:22:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the privilege of participating \Nin the fulfillment of the psalmist’s words: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.02,0:22:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah gives the command; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.52,0:22:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the women proclaiming \Nthe good news are a large army.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.22,0:22:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of our sisters have been active \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for many years \Nin that “large army” of women. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.80,0:23:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Bertille Kupelian, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.80,0:23:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a special pioneer in West Virginia, \Nin the United States, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.70,0:23:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,entered the full-time service in 1958. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.51,0:23:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In that time, she’s helped \Nmore than 60 people to baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.91,0:23:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How has her outlook toward the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.31,0:23:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,kept her going for almost 60 years?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.66,0:23:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was opposed  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the truth as I was growing up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.43,0:23:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but my mother was very, very zealous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew the things my mother \Nwas teaching me was the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.00,0:23:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that this was \Nwhat I was going to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.54,0:23:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was not easy, but we did it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.25,0:23:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I was Daddy’s girl, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.88,0:23:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but my mom made sure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.22,0:24:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that I and my siblings knew the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.22,0:24:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And she studied with us \Nwhen no other children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.53,0:24:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation \Nhad Bible studies at home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.53,0:24:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we kind of kicked \Nand didn’t like it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.54,0:24:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was glad she did it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.74,0:24:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother was a very, very positive person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.41,0:24:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and although she had the opposition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.55,0:24:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw how she dealt with it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.38,0:24:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and how firm and determined she was. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.12,0:24:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was something she taught us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.82,0:24:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a mind-set. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.36,0:24:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nyour mind is a wonderful thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.79,0:24:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It can really influence you \Ntoward good or maybe not so good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.20,0:24:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, \NI was determined in my mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was going to serve Jehovah then.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.91,0:24:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In our congregation, there were brothers \Nand sisters of the anointed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.25,0:24:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They were always very kind to me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.85,0:25:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and they encouraged me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.35,0:25:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked in service with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.62,0:25:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, \N‘That’s the way I want to be.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.73,0:25:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Children like attention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.60,0:25:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, if you give them attention\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.03,0:25:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—you talk with them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.03,0:25:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask if you could work \Nwith them in the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.47,0:25:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and help them prepare a presentation\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.64,0:25:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and go over it and over it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.81,0:25:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they’re ready for the ministry\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.68,0:25:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—then they’ll enjoy it more.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.58,0:25:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That was one of the things \Nthat the anointed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.42,0:25:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,did in the congregation where I was. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.42,0:25:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They paid attention to me, and I loved it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.79,0:25:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How I learned to teach \Nwas I think about the person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.16,0:25:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think about their situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.00,0:25:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I try to think in my mind \Nwhat they are thinking, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.50,0:25:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I work on that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:26:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and think of what kind of scriptures \NI can find to help them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.81,0:26:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.18,0:26:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to pattern our studies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.18,0:26:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to incorporate some of those things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.16,0:26:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There are always challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.86,0:26:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the winters right on the lake \Nwhere I lived were very harsh. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.73,0:26:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And my trailer was parked \Nin such a way that every time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.77,0:26:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the wind blew \Nand the snow came and the ice came, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.01,0:26:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it sealed the door. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.01,0:26:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, I carried a big knife in my car, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.74,0:26:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would have to cut around the door \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.18,0:26:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the door to open\N—break the ice seal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.68,0:26:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was interesting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.05,0:26:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I had some opposition in the territories, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.79,0:26:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and one was this lady who was very irate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.29,0:26:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And she went to kick me, \Nand she kicked me right in the stomach, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.80,0:26:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and so then, anyway, \NI dismissed myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.23,0:27:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, a while later, \Nit was time to work the territory again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.70,0:27:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wanted to go there, \Nand we didn’t have do-not-calls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.84,0:27:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think, at that time, \Nat least there wasn’t any in the territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.58,0:27:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So then anyway, I called by \Nand I mentioned to her:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.51,0:27:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,, “Why, hello there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.52,0:27:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I’ve had the opportunity \Nto talk with you before.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.15,0:27:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she remembered. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.15,0:27:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, “Well, perhaps \Nyou were having a bad day that day.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.59,0:27:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I hit a lull when I had few Bible studies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.16,0:27:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I prayed diligently to Jehovah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.60,0:27:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah, help me. \NI need Bible studies.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.04,0:27:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you have to be \Nout there looking for them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.21,0:27:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’ve lost my father, my mother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.48,0:27:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,my sister, my brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.98,0:27:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, naturally you feel at a loss, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.78,0:27:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah strengthened me, \Nand the friends strengthened me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.29,0:27:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and I kept busy in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.52,0:27:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But again, it goes back to that mind-set. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.56,0:28:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to let the challenge beat you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.96,0:28:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or are you going to beat the challenge?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.30,0:28:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Jehovah can beat the challenge.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.70,0:28:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, discouragement \Nis one of Satan’s biggest tools. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.91,0:28:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always tell myself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.21,0:28:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m not going to let Satan beat me down.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.38,0:28:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as health is concerned, \Nmy everyday health is very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.55,0:28:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have a leg that drives me crazy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.42,0:28:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think back to Jacob. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.83,0:28:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He served Jehovah with a limp. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.23,0:28:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I think of Paul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.40,0:28:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, those things keep you humble.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.77,0:28:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve prayed and prayed and prayed about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.78,0:28:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but just like with the apostle Paul, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.24,0:28:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it didn’t disappear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.65,0:28:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, I just say: \N“Patch me up till Armageddon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.28,0:28:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll disappear then.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.29,0:29:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If your mind is made up \Nthat this is what you’re going to do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.49,0:29:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,this is your life, \Nthis is what Jehovah wants you to do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.49,0:29:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and so then you do it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.86,0:29:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve seen how he’s kept me going. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.80,0:29:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that I’ve needed work; \NI’ve needed money; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.64,0:29:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve needed strength. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.88,0:29:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve needed companionship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.88,0:29:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because a lot of times \NI’m in the ministry by myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.61,0:29:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I talk to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.62,0:29:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, he’s always there for me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.15,0:29:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I definitely want to keep pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.59,0:29:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or serving Jehovah the best I can, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.39,0:29:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of what comes up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.66,0:29:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing more joyful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.10,0:29:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than to see that you have helped \Nsomebody to live forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.17,0:29:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how much better could it be?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.61,0:30:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Kupelian had a profound effect\Non those she witnessed to. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.42,0:30:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this because she found me \Nin the door-to-door ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.62,0:30:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was 14 years old. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.06,0:30:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At that age, I had the goal to be a doctor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.26,0:30:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One night after the meeting, \NBertille said to me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.07,0:30:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, you know, \Nin the new world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.57,0:30:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we won’t need doctors \Nbecause Jesus will do all the healing.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.44,0:30:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, that hit me hard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.78,0:30:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wanted to help people \Nas well as provide for my mother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.81,0:30:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But she added, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.82,0:30:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“What we will need are teachers.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.72,0:30:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that was a good idea. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.25,0:30:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Still focused on a career, \NI had one type of teacher in mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.69,0:30:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but she had another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.73,0:30:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Through her patience and reasoning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.76,0:30:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,she helped me to become \Nthe most important kind of teacher\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.13,0:30:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—a teacher of God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.47,0:31:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there someone like Sister Kupelian \Nin your congregation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.11,0:31:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We are grateful \Nfor these sisters’ zealous spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.81,0:31:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the personal interest \Nthey show toward us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.78,0:31:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re sure Jehovah \Nvalues them like we do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.59,0:31:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,One of Sister Kupelian’s strengths \Nis her perseverance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.89,0:31:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Perseverance means to continue resolutely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.09,0:31:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in the face of adversity, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.10,0:31:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,being tenacious, not giving up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.10,0:31:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If not careful, \Nwe could reach a spiritual goal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.14,0:31:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,only to let something \Ndistract us away from it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.31,0:31:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.31,0:31:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a young sister is pioneering \Nand working toward new goals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.68,0:31:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How, though, \Nis she in danger of losing her focus?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.30,0:31:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started learning sign language, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.46,0:31:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it just seemed to come natural for me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.04,0:32:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,After I transferred to the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.94,0:32:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember feeling so happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.06,0:32:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pioneering and really enjoying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.19,0:32:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this new way of communicating.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.60,0:32:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s funny how \Nthe thing you love can also be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.64,0:32:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing that tests you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.41,0:32:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, I took the test \Nfor a sign-language interpreter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.21,0:32:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe I passed!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.55,0:32:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved my new job.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.12,0:32:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My hope was \Nthat it would support my pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.29,0:32:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.29,0:33:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,allow me to travel one day to a country \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.43,0:33:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and preach where there was \Na need for sign language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.80,0:33:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My boss was very happy with my work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.04,0:33:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so much so that he began to give me more.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.64,0:33:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone seemed appreciative, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.05,0:33:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the extra money didn’t hurt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.43,0:33:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was handling it all fine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.30,0:33:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh, OK, for a while.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.78,0:34:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My boss asked me to work full-time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.79,0:34:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for a few months \Nto get some extra training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.89,0:34:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The raise could help me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.96,0:34:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with planning my trip abroad.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.73,0:34:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew my parents would be concerned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.74,0:34:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew because I felt it too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.31,0:34:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was already dragging physically. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.14,0:34:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But then again, \Nit would only be for a few months. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.58,0:35:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really torn.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.48,0:35:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad kindly commended me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.49,0:35:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for having good goals \Nand trying my best to work toward them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.16,0:35:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he showed me \Na scripture that really helped me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.33,0:35:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Timothy 4:16: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.13,0:35:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Pay constant attention \Nto yourself and to your teaching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.73,0:35:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“Persevere in these things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.24,0:35:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“for by doing this \Nyou will save both yourself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.21,0:35:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and those who listen to you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.71,0:35:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He helped me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.71,0:35:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to see that Timothy set spiritual goals \Nfor himself while growing up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.18,0:35:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But Paul was now telling him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.69,0:35:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t stop!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.52,0:35:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Timothy \Nwas a grown spiritual man, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.46,0:35:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul encouraged him \Nto continue setting new spiritual goals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.90,0:35:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, to ‘persevere in them.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.77,0:35:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What was I persevering in?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.08,0:36:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I kindly turned down the offer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.92,0:36:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and explained to my boss \Nthat I’d like to keep my hours \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.75,0:36:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to a minimum \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.86,0:36:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so I could support \Nmy number one job.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.20,0:36:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It might take me longer to save my money, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.91,0:36:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’ll make that trip one day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.74,0:36:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah’s help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.64,0:36:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and a little perseverance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.05,0:36:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting \Nthat the skill she used \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.22,0:36:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand her ministry \Nand support her pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.06,0:36:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,became her distraction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.39,0:36:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn’t easy for her to see at first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.56,0:36:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Who helped her to see the problem clearly? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.33,0:37:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was her parents, \Nespecially her spiritually-minded father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.00,0:37:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The interest you family heads \Nshow in your daughters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.24,0:37:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is well worth the effort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.61,0:37:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It can point them in the right direction \Nwhen they need guidance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.78,0:37:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you do for them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.65,0:37:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,shows how precious they are \Nto you and to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.42,0:37:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s the feeling \Nexpressed in the music video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.86,0:37:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious Daughter.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.77,0:37:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Through all her tender years,\NHe watched her grow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.41,0:37:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Many the joys and tears,\NShe would come to know.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.22,0:37:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But when she gave her best\NAnd came through each test,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.29,0:38:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She made His heart feel so good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.23,0:38:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious daughter, \NHe’s so proud of you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.95,0:38:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Time won’t alter His love for you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.70,0:38:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard work and sacrifice—\NThat’s just her way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.91,0:39:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking of His advice\NHelps her through the day,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.72,0:39:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And she’s so glad to know\NThat He loves her so.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.63,0:39:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It means so much to hear him say:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.70,0:39:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Precious daughter, \NI’m so proud of you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.05,0:39:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Time won’t alter my love for you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.93,0:39:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah sees\NAnd Jehovah knows\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.17,0:39:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All the work you’ve done\NAnd the love you’ve shown.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.01,0:40:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, He won’t forget\NHow you’ve loved His name\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.02,0:40:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For all this time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.99,0:40:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious daughter, \NHe’s so proud of you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.13,0:40:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious daughter, \NHe’ll be there for you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.35,0:40:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious daughter, \NHe will care for you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.99,0:40:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious daughter,\NHe loves you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.22,0:41:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle John wrote \Nthat he had no greater joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.66,0:41:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,than to hear that his spiritual children \Ncontinued “walking in the truth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.66,0:41:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You fathers feel that same joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.63,0:41:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see your daughters \Nmature as Christian women. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.44,0:41:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Raising your children to love Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.27,0:41:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is just one of the many things \Nyou do for your family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.01,0:41:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,At a Bethel morning worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.21,0:41:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lett focused \Non the special relationship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.32,0:41:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,between a husband and wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.65,0:41:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What can a husband do to show \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.65,0:41:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that he shares Jehovah’s view of his wife?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.42,0:41:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My theme for this little discussion is\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.79,0:41:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Husbands, Love Your Wife as Yourself.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.50,0:42:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Jesus say \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.50,0:42:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was the second greatest commandment? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.64,0:42:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nyou’re familiar with it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.81,0:42:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew 22:39, \Nhe said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.14,0:42:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must love \Nyour neighbor as yourself.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.41,0:42:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nwhat an excellent illustration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.98,0:42:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is contained\Nin this second greatest commandment!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.72,0:42:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about it, \Nwe just naturally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.52,0:42:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,inherently, love ourselves, \Ndon’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.99,0:42:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we show \Nlove in many ways. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.46,0:42:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus is saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.96,0:42:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Work hard to show\Nthe same love for others\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.50,0:42:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you show for yourself.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.53,0:42:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But, now, thinking of husbands\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.60,0:42:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as addressed in our theme, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.67,0:42:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,who is a husband’s closest neighbor? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.54,0:42:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, his wife.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.54,0:42:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So especially must a husband work hard\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.61,0:42:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to show the love that he shows \Nfor himself just naturally and then \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.88,0:42:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to show that love for his wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.08,0:42:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what are some specific ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.79,0:42:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that husbands \Njust naturally love themselves? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.96,0:42:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, \Nlet’s talk about five. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.83,0:43:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And undoubtedly\Nyou can think of many others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.23,0:43:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that could be discussed\Nduring this discussion.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.10,0:43:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But number one: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.13,0:43:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A husband feeds himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.34,0:43:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 5:29 says in part: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.67,0:43:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“For no man ever hated his own body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.04,0:43:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but he feeds . . . it.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.85,0:43:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does loving our wife, \Nnow, as ourself require? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.28,0:43:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing, \Nwe certainly would make sure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.49,0:43:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we provide for the food \Nand for other material needs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.39,0:43:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that our wife has. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.56,0:43:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And regarding this, \NI think of our brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.90,0:43:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in concentration camps \Nin Nazi Germany. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.73,0:43:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Food was very scarce. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.80,0:43:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But our brothers, even then, \Nfrom their meager food ration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.71,0:43:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,would share food \Nwith other brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.84,0:43:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,even, in some cases, \Nwith worldly people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.48,0:43:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, similarly, \Na husband would do without himself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.18,0:43:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if necessary, in order to provide \Nwhat his wife really needs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.15,0:44:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But even more importantly, \Nan extended application, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.22,0:44:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he would make sure \Nthat she is well-fed spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.86,0:44:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He must make sure \Nthat she has opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.93,0:44:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to benefit from periods \Nof personal study, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.93,0:44:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,congregation meetings, \Nassemblies, conventions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.60,0:44:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and family worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.77,0:44:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s talk \Nabout a second way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.11,0:44:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that a husband \Njust naturally loves himself: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.04,0:44:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We cherish ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.31,0:44:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 5:29 says in part: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.39,0:44:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“For no man ever hated his own body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.96,0:44:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but he . . . cherishes it.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.39,0:44:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nwhat does cherish mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.59,0:44:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, \Naccording to the dictionary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.60,0:44:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to treat \Nwith affection and tenderness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.03,0:44:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,treasure, value, \Nattach importance to. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.54,0:44:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because of this feeling \Nwe have toward ourselves, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.94,0:44:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we try to get rest \Nwhen we’re sick or tired; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.65,0:45:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we try to be \Nwith friends and loved ones; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.62,0:45:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we play games; we exercise; \Nwe do things we enjoy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.29,0:45:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Periodically, \Nwe treat ourselves, don’t we,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.59,0:45:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because we cherish ourselves? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.39,0:45:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does loving \Nour wife as ourself require? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.26,0:45:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it certainly means more\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.13,0:45:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,than just being able \Nto put up with our mate.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.33,0:45:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It means cherishing her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.80,0:45:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,cultivating affection, \Nor fondness, for her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.71,0:45:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of this: \NAt Proverbs 8:31, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.58,0:45:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it says that Jesus \Nin his prehuman existence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.31,0:45:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was fond of humans.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.22,0:45:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don’t you think \Nthat fondness he had for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.15,0:45:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,made it easier for him\Nto come to the earth,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.16,0:45:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,take the difficult assignment he took, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.19,0:45:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and even die for us \Nbecause he was fond of us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.96,0:45:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, similarly,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.96,0:45:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if wives are cherished \Nby their husbands\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.10,0:45:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—if husbands \Nare fond of their wives—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.30,0:45:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it’ll make it so much easier \Nto forgive them,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.51,0:46:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to even die for them, \Nif necessary, in the future. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.51,0:46:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we’re going to have \Nthis proper feeling, like Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.58,0:46:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to focus \Non the good qualities of our wife, see,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.42,0:46:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,not the flaws, the imperfections. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.29,0:46:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And as one \Nof the brothers commented on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.96,0:46:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,(I love the thoughts \Nin The Watchtower comments): \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.73,0:46:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“Love is best sensed \Nwhen it is expressed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.80,0:46:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“How vital that marriage mates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.83,0:46:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“not allow the activities of daily life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.27,0:46:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to rob them of exchanging \Nexpressions of affection!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.07,0:46:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s get a third way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.08,0:46:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that husbands \Njust naturally love themselves: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.25,0:46:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We adorn ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.18,0:46:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,First Timothy 2:9 speaks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.22,0:46:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of women “adorn[ing] themselves \Nin appropriate dress.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.69,0:46:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, husbands \Ntry to do the same thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.69,0:46:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And in adorning ourselves,\Nwe try to cover over\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.46,0:46:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and minimize our flaws \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.43,0:47:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and cover our bulges, \Nour blemishes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.27,0:47:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to make ourselves \Nlook as good as possible, don’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.31,0:47:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does loving \Nour wife as ourself require? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.38,0:47:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, we certainly \Nwouldn’t shine a spotlight on her flaws. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.15,0:47:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn’t do this \Nin the presence of others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.15,0:47:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We would try hard \Nnot to even do it in our own mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.62,0:47:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, we seek to cover over \Nminor sins and transgressions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.26,0:47:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as encouraged at Proverbs 19:11, \Nwhere it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.96,0:47:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is beauty . . . to overlook an offense.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.27,0:47:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we work hard\Nto adorn our wives\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.04,0:47:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—make her look \Nas good as possible—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.44,0:47:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the eyes of others, \Neven in our own mind.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.01,0:47:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s get a fourth way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.01,0:47:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that husbands \Njust naturally love themselves: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.35,0:47:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We take steps to heal ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.08,0:47:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re sick or injured. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.42,0:47:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark 5:26 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.45,0:47:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,talks about a woman \Nwho was very sick. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.46,0:47:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘She suffered at the hands \Nof many physicians; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.69,0:48:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‘she spent all her resources; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.39,0:48:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn’t get any better; \Nshe got worse.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.40,0:48:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But the point is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.40,0:48:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,she was really trying hard \Nto heal herself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.50,0:48:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, husbands \Ntry to do the same thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.97,0:48:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we’re sick or injured, \Nwe try to get extra rest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.27,0:48:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll buy medicine,\Nwe’ll take vitamins,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.28,0:48:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll make an appointment \Nwith the doctor, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.65,0:48:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll pursue therapy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.98,0:48:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we try to get well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.78,0:48:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What does loving our wife \Nas ourself require then? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.05,0:48:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we would certainly \Ndo all within our power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.29,0:48:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if she’s sick or injured \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.29,0:48:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to help her get well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.29,0:48:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But even more importantly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.30,0:48:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if she happens \Nto be ailing somewhat spiritually, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.86,0:48:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we would do everything \Nwe can possibly do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.83,0:48:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to help her get well spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.30,0:48:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What would be something, \Nperhaps, we could do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.31,0:48:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Proverbs 12:18 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.64,0:48:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“The tongue of the wise is a healing”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.01,0:48:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—so the using of wise expressions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.52,0:48:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Proverbs 16:24: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.68,0:49:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Pleasant sayings are a honeycomb, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.12,0:49:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“sweet to the soul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.12,0:49:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and a healing to the bones.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.19,0:49:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, “pleasant sayings,” \Nwe would use these \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.23,0:49:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to help her \Nget well spiritually.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.63,0:49:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But now here’s one more, \Na fifth way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.17,0:49:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that husbands \Njust naturally love themselves: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.07,0:49:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We make allowances,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.21,0:49:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,excuses, \Nif we make mistakes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.04,0:49:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands who make mistakes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.68,0:49:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are often heard blaming it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.31,0:49:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,on their heredity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.45,0:49:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe the environment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.92,0:49:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,their blood-sugar level, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.16,0:49:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,how much sleep they got \Nor didn’t get the night before, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.63,0:49:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the weather, and so forth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.06,0:49:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We tend to well understand \Nour own limitations, don’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.17,0:49:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we allow for that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.17,0:49:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what about \Nloving our wife as ourself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.44,0:49:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d make the same allowances for her\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.64,0:49:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—being positive, \Nimputing good motives to her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.91,0:50:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If she speaks a little roughly \Nor acts a little thoughtlessly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.08,0:50:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll try to discern the feelings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.58,0:50:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the words or actions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.12,0:50:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll make allowance, \Nespecially if we can discern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.76,0:50:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that she’s under some kind \Nof emotional pressure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.80,0:50:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll make that allowance for her \Nlike we would for ourselves.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.60,0:50:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there we have five ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.60,0:50:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that we as husbands \Nshow love for ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.20,0:50:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We feed, cherish, adorn, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.84,0:50:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,try to heal ourselves; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.91,0:50:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and we make allowances, excuses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.75,0:50:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when we make mistakes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.48,0:50:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s work hard \Nto show the same love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.52,0:50:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in those five areas \Nfor our dear, beloved wives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.32,0:50:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m sure, as we said, \Nyou can think of other ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.29,0:50:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that husbands just naturally \Nlove themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.96,0:50:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But what a rich illustration Jesus gave! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.50,0:50:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And interestingly, \Nhe took it even a step further. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.00,0:50:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He further expanded the illustration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.84,0:51:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at John 13:34. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.67,0:51:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re familiar with this, 13:34. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.38,0:51:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: \N“I am giving you a new commandment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.55,0:51:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you love one another; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.22,0:51:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as I have loved you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.25,0:51:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you also love one another.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.62,0:51:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So he’s saying that we should have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.56,0:51:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,even deeper love for our brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.59,0:51:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—which would definitely \Ninclude our Christian wives—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.66,0:51:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a deeper love \Nthan we have for ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.17,0:51:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that deeper love \Nwould move us to treat \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.27,0:51:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,our dear wives even better\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.64,0:51:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than we treat ourselves.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.24,0:51:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands, we know your wife \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.71,0:51:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,will never grow tired \Nof your efforts to apply that counsel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.82,0:51:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the whole family \Nbenefits when each member \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.39,0:51:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,loves their closest neighbor \Nas themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.49,0:51:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And when a family \Nis happy and spiritually strong, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.86,0:51:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they can do so much for Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.80,0:52:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At the Scandinavia branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.17,0:52:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,families from 19 congregations \Nin Denmark, Norway, and Sweden \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.91,0:52:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,participated in children’s choruses \Nto record theocratic music. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.31,0:52:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The children worked hard \Nto prepare for each session, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.38,0:52:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but that meant hard work \Nfor the parents too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.72,0:52:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The results, however, \Nare a chorus of praise to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.46,0:52:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You get so happy \Nwhen you sing with others!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.80,0:52:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah created us like that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.21,0:52:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The birds also sing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.78,0:52:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that Jehovah is proud of me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.82,0:52:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scandinavia branch office \Nsupervises nine languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.69,0:52:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in audio and video production. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.99,0:52:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the three largest languages\N—Swedish, Norwegian, and Danish—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.76,0:53:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there are also three children choruses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.16,0:53:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that help us \Nwith the recordings of the songs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.76,0:53:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Become Jehovah’s Friend series.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.37,0:53:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I listen very carefully \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.34,0:53:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to the American adult chorus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.27,0:53:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to spot where they breathe, \Nwhere they pause, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.71,0:53:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the overall mood\Nin their way of singing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.18,0:53:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I listen \Nto the music we have received.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.85,0:53:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a piano at home \Nto practice the voices and figure out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.46,0:53:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where the high notes and low notes are, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.89,0:53:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where the challenging parts are, \Nand how I can pass this on to the children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.46,0:53:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I also think about what the goal\Nwith the recording is\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.23,0:53:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—how other children who listen to the song \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.57,0:53:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,can feel the same joy as we feel\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.70,0:53:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are singing and recording it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.38,0:53:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the children arrive,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.95,0:53:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we make sure that all the equipment \Nis prepared and tested \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.65,0:53:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that everything \Nis ready when they come here.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.12,0:54:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When we receive \Nthe assignment to participate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.76,0:54:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the recordings of a new song, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.79,0:54:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that our girls have been \Nfull of initiative to practice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.56,0:54:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have made it our custom\Nto sing the songs at our family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.60,0:54:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When we are driving, \Nlike to the RTO \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.77,0:54:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for the recordings and on other occasions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.24,0:54:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we usually sing in the car.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.61,0:54:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I like to sing the songs\Nbecause they are good\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.75,0:54:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and have nice melodies.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.95,0:54:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I especially like the new songs\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.12,0:54:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are so different.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.19,0:54:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One has African drums in it,\Nand the next is a bit Irish\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.96,0:54:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and like you are walking\Nin a valley and on a mountain.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.86,0:54:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Alma plays the cello\Nand has asked to get the sheet music\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.30,0:54:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the new Kingdom songs,\Nwhich are her favorites right now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.84,0:54:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a challenge for André and me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.74,0:54:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are not that musical.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.91,0:55:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There is also a serious part,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.95,0:55:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so we start with a prayer to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.29,0:55:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we watch the video and talk\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.62,0:55:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about the point of the video\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.86,0:55:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and how other children and families\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.16,0:55:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,can benefit when listening to them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.30,0:55:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we need to loosen up a bit,\Nso we warm up with some exercises,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.87,0:55:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we’re ready to sing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.87,0:55:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It is clear to us that they appreciate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.53,0:55:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,their privilege more and more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.54,0:56:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually see it as praise to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.81,0:56:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy they have of singing for Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.38,0:56:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rubs off on us who work with them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.05,0:56:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When the children sing with joy\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.62,0:56:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and express themselves freely,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.62,0:56:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it has an effect on us as parents\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.62,0:56:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ones in the congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.63,0:56:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah becomes happy when he sees it,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.09,0:56:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and also many brothers and sisters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.03,0:56:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and children become happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.03,0:56:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is fun to make the recordings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.03,0:56:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You get so happy,\Nand then it’s more fun\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.84,0:56:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to sing at the meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.01,0:56:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see more clearly why we sing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.64,0:56:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and why it is a part of our worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.35,0:56:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t go there just\Nto spend time with our friends;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.35,0:56:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we go there to sing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.35,0:56:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a part of praising Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.79,0:56:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Singing is like a prayer to him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.19,0:56:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been humming the songs,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.39,0:56:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and people around me wonder\Nwhat it is I am always humming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.73,0:57:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it has helped me,\Nand it is an easy way to give a witness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.80,0:57:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My faith in Jehovah is stronger now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.01,0:57:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that I am happier\Nknowing Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.58,0:57:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,after I began singing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.78,0:57:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand that singing\Nis a huge part of our worship,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.05,0:57:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah wants us to use it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.75,0:57:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When children sing out joyfully to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.09,0:57:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they draw closer to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.16,0:57:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The choruses in Scandinavia \Nare a good example of that fact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.20,0:57:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Their excitement for singing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.70,0:57:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,even gave them opportunities \Nto witness to their classmates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.97,0:57:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably already include singing \Nas part of your family worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.64,0:57:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and agree that we feel \Na special warmth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.08,0:57:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when the family sings \Nto Jehovah together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.32,0:57:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As you look ahead \Nat the August midweek meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.59,0:57:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll notice a part \Nfor the week of August 28 that asks: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.59,0:58:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“When Can I Next Serve \Nas an Auxiliary Pioneer?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.10,0:58:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll want to prepare \Nby watching the video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.00,0:58:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah, I Can Do Almost Anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.00,0:58:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the life story \Nof Sister Sabina Hernández, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.17,0:58:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which appeared \Nin the December 2015 program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.61,0:58:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find it \Nin the Video on Demand section \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.81,0:58:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,under “Interviews and Experiences.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.32,0:58:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At the midweek meeting, \Nyou’ll be ready to share \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.69,0:58:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how Sabina’s example encouraged you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.39,0:58:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Our program has shown us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.39,0:58:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,how much Jehovah values \Nwhat women do in the family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.93,0:58:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation, and in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.10,0:58:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To all of our sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.60,0:58:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,please be assured that we love you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.21,0:58:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s our prayer \Nthat Jehovah continues to bless your work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.04,0:58:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to conclude with greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.05,0:58:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,from our brothers and sisters \Non the island of Saipan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.22,0:59:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of Micronesia, \Nin the western Pacific Ocean, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.95,0:59:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Saipan is a popular destination \Nfor thousands of tourists. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.09,0:59:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But make no mistake, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.09,0:59:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a preacher’s paradise.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.40,0:59:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After early opposition \Nto the preaching work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.27,0:59:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is now flourishing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.80,0:59:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with an average \Nof 200 Kingdom publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.37,0:59:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in three congregations \Nthroughout the island, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.04,0:59:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,including 33 regular pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.11,0:59:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The relaxing atmosphere \Nand tropical climate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.82,0:59:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,make public witnessing carts \Nan effective way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.52,0:59:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach the hearts of receptive ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.29,0:59:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The large number of tourists\N—many from Asian lands—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.19,0:59:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are finding our literature \Nin Japanese, Korean, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.03,0:59:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Tagalog, Chinese, \Nand other languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.90,0:59:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the first baptized publishers \Nin Saipan \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.37,0:59:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are faithful sisters who are now \Nin their 80’s. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.84,0:59:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Taeko Castro \Nwas baptized in 1970, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.01,1:00:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and Tomasa Mafnas \Nwas baptized in 1973. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.18,1:00:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They continue to be \Nzealous Kingdom proclaimers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.89,1:00:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and are fine examples \Nof “the women proclaiming the good news.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.56,1:00:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We send our love and greetings \Nto these congregations in Saipan \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.53,1:00:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and warmly commend them \Nfor their positive spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.63,1:00:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and hard work \Nto make Jehovah’s name known. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.27,1:00:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.60,1:00:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.61,1:00:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.\N
